111static void assign( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &name,
112 std::map<gun_mode_id, gun_modifier_data> &mods )
113{
114 if( !jo.has_array( name ) ) {
115 return;
116 }
117 mods.clear();
118 for( JsonArray curr : jo.get_array( name ) ) {
119 mods.emplace( gun_mode_id( curr.get_string( 0 ) ), gun_modifier_data( curr.get_string( 1 ),
120 curr.get_int( 2 ), curr.size() >= 4 ? curr.get_tags( 3 ) : std::set<std::string>() ) );
121 }
122}

124static bool assign_coverage_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &key,
125 body_part_set &parts, bool &sided )
126{
127 auto parse = [&parts, &sided]( const std::string & val_in ) {
128 const std::string &val = json_report_strict
129 ? val_in
130 : to_lower_case( val_in );
131 if( val == "arms" || val == "arm_either" ) {
132 parts.set( bp_arm_l );
133 parts.set( bp_arm_r );
134 } else if( val == "hands" || val == "hand_either" ) {
135 parts.set( bp_hand_l );
136 parts.set( bp_hand_r );
137 } else if( val == "legs" || val == "leg_either" ) {
138 parts.set( bp_leg_l );
139 parts.set( bp_leg_r );
140 } else if( val == "feet" || val == "foot_either" ) {
141 parts.set( bp_foot_l );
142 parts.set( bp_foot_r );
143 } else {
144 parts.set( get_body_part_token( val ) );
145 }
146 sided |= val == "arm_either" || val == "hand_either" ||
147 val == "leg_either" || val == "foot_either";
148 };
149
150 if( jo.has_array( key ) ) {
151 for( const std::string line : jo.get_array( key ) ) {
152 parse( line );
153 }
154 return true;
155
156 } else if( jo.has_string( key ) ) {
157 parse( jo.get_string( key ) );
158 return true;
159
160 } else {
161 return false;
162 }

165void Item_factory::finalize_pre( itype &obj )
166{
167 // TODO: separate repairing from reinforcing/enhancement
168 if( obj.damage_max() == obj.damage_min() ) {
169 obj.item_tags.insert( "NO_REPAIR" );
170 }
171
172 if( obj.has_flag( "STAB" ) || obj.has_flag( "SPEAR" ) ) {
173 std::swap( obj.melee[DT_CUT], obj.melee[DT_STAB] );
174 }
175
176 // add usage methods (with default values) based upon qualities
177 // if a method was already set the specific values remain unchanged
178 for( const auto &q : obj.qualities ) {
179 for( const auto &u : q.first.obj().usages ) {
180 if( q.second >= u.first ) {
181 emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, u.second );
182 }
183 }
184 }
185
186 if( obj.mod ) {
187 std::string func = obj.gunmod ? "GUNMOD_ATTACH" : "TOOLMOD_ATTACH";
188 emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, func );
189 } else if( obj.gun ) {
190 const std::string func = "detach_gunmods";
191 emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, func );
192 }
193
194 if( get_option<bool>( "NO_FAULTS" ) ) {
195 obj.faults.clear();
196 }
197
198 // If no category was forced via JSON automatically calculate one now
199 if( !obj.category_force.is_valid() || obj.category_force.is_empty() ) {
200 obj.category_force = calc_category( obj );
201 }
202
203 // use pre-cataclysm price as default if post-cataclysm price unspecified
204 if( obj.price_post < 0_cent ) {
205 obj.price_post = obj.price;
206 }
207 // use base volume if integral volume unspecified
208 if( obj.integral_volume < 0_ml ) {
209 obj.integral_volume = obj.volume;
210 }
211 // use base weight if integral weight unspecified
212 if( obj.integral_weight < 0_gram ) {
213 obj.integral_weight = obj.weight;
214 }
215 // for ammo and comestibles stack size defaults to count of initial charges
216 // Set max stack size to 200 to prevent integer overflow
217 if( obj.count_by_charges() ) {
218 if( obj.stack_size == 0 ) {
219 obj.stack_size = obj.charges_default();
220 } else if( obj.stack_size > 200 ) {
221 debugmsg( obj.id.str() + " stack size is too large, reducing to 200" );
222 obj.stack_size = 200;
223 }
224 }
225
226 // Items always should have some volume.
227 // TODO: handle possible exception software?
228 // TODO: make items with 0 volume an error during loading?
229 if( obj.volume <= 0_ml ) {
230 obj.volume = units::from_milliliter( 1 );
231 }
232
233 // set light_emission based on LIGHT_[X] flag
234 for( const auto &f : obj.item_tags ) {
235 int ll;
236 if( sscanf( f.c_str(), "LIGHT_%i", &ll ) == 1 && ll > 0 ) {
237 obj.light_emission = ll;
238 }
239 }
240 // remove LIGHT_[X] flags
241 erase_if( obj.item_tags, []( const std::string & f ) {
242 return f.find( "LIGHT_" ) == 0;
243 } );
244
245 // Set max volume for containers to prevent integer overflow
246 if( obj.container && obj.container->contains > 10000_liter ) {
247 debugmsg( obj.id.str() + " storage volume is too large, reducing to 10000 liters" );
248 obj.container->contains = 10000_liter;
249 }
250
251 if( obj.ammo ) {
252 // for ammo not specifying loudness (or an explicit zero) derive value from other properties
253 if( obj.ammo->loudness < 0 ) {
254 obj.ammo->loudness = obj.ammo->range * 2;
255 for( const damage_unit &du : obj.ammo->damage ) {
256 obj.ammo->loudness += ( du.amount + du.res_pen ) * 2;
257 }
258 }
259
260 const auto &mats = obj.materials;
261 if( std::find( mats.begin(), mats.end(), material_id( "hydrocarbons" ) ) == mats.end() &&
262 std::find( mats.begin(), mats.end(), material_id( "oil" ) ) == mats.end() ) {
263 const auto &ammo_effects = obj.ammo->ammo_effects;
264 obj.ammo->cookoff = ammo_effects.count( ammo_effect_INCENDIARY ) > 0 ||
265 ammo_effects.count( ammo_effect_COOKOFF ) > 0;
266 static const std::set<ammo_effect_str_id> special_cookoff_tags = {{
267 ammo_effect_EXPLOSIVE, ammo_effect_EXPLOSIVE_BIG, ammo_effect_EXPLOSIVE_HUGE, ammo_effect_EXPLOSIVE_SMALL, ammo_effect_FLASHBANG, ammo_effect_FRAG, ammo_effect_NAPALM, ammo_effect_NAPALM_BIG, ammo_effect_SMOKE, ammo_effect_SMOKE_BIG, ammo_effect_TOXICGAS,
268 }
269 };
270 obj.ammo->special_cookoff = std::any_of( ammo_effects.begin(), ammo_effects.end(),
271 []( const ammo_effect_str_id & ae_id ) {
272 return special_cookoff_tags.count( ae_id ) > 0;
273 } );
274 } else {
275 obj.ammo->cookoff = false;
276 obj.ammo->special_cookoff = false;
277 }
278
279 for( auto iter = obj.ammo->ammo_effects.begin(); iter != obj.ammo->ammo_effects.end(); ) {
280 const ammo_effect_str_id &ae_id = *iter;
281 if( ae_id.is_valid() ) {
282 iter++;
283 } else {
284 int dummy = 0;
285 if( sscanf( ae_id.c_str(), "RECOVER_%i", &dummy ) == 1 ) {
286 obj.ammo->dont_recover_one_in *= dummy;
287 } else {
288 debugmsg( "%s has unknown ammo_effect %s, removing", obj.id, ae_id );
289 }
290
291 iter = obj.ammo->ammo_effects.erase( iter );
292 }
293 }
294 }
295 const auto check_ammo_effects = []( const itype_id & id, std::set<ammo_effect_str_id> &effects ) {
296 for( auto iter = effects.begin(); iter != effects.end(); ) {
297 const ammo_effect_str_id &ae_id = *iter;
298 if( ae_id.is_valid() ) {
299 iter++;
300 } else {
301 debugmsg( "%s has unknown ammo_effect %s, removing", id, ae_id );
302 iter = effects.erase( iter );
303 }
304 }
305 };
306 if( obj.gun ) {
307 check_ammo_effects( obj.id, obj.gun->ammo_effects );
308 }
309 if( obj.gunmod ) {
310 check_ammo_effects( obj.id, obj.gunmod->ammo_effects );
311 }

313 // Helper for ammo migration in following sections
314 auto migrate_ammo_set = [&]( std::set<ammotype> &ammoset ) {
315 for( auto ammo_type_it = ammoset.begin(); ammo_type_it != ammoset.end(); ) {
316 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( ammo_type_it->obj().default_ammotype() );
317 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
318 ammo_type_it = ammoset.erase( ammo_type_it );
319 ammoset.insert( ammoset.begin(), maybe_migrated->second );
320 } else {
321 ++ammo_type_it;
322 }
323 }
324 };
325
326 if( obj.magazine ) {
327 // ensure default_ammo is set
328 if( obj.magazine->default_ammo.is_null() ) {
329 obj.magazine->default_ammo = ammotype( *obj.magazine->type.begin() )->default_ammotype();
330 }
331
332 // If the magazine has ammo types for which the default ammo has been migrated, we need to
333 // replace those ammo types with that of the migrated ammo
334 migrate_ammo_set( obj.magazine->type );
335
336 // ensure default_ammo is migrated if need be
337 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( obj.magazine->default_ammo );
338 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
339 obj.magazine->default_ammo = maybe_migrated->second.obj().default_ammotype();
340 }
341 }
342
343 // Migrate compataible magazines
344 for( auto kv : obj.magazines ) {
345 for( auto mag_it = kv.second.begin(); mag_it != kv.second.end(); ) {
346 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_magazines.find( *mag_it );
347 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_magazines.end() ) {
348 mag_it = kv.second.erase( mag_it );
349 kv.second.insert( kv.second.begin(), maybe_migrated->second );
350 } else {
351 ++mag_it;
352 }
353 }
354 }
355
356 // Migrate default magazines
357 for( auto kv : obj.magazine_default ) {
358 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_magazines.find( kv.second );
359 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_magazines.end() ) {
360 kv.second = maybe_migrated->second;
361 }
362 }
363
364 if( obj.mod ) {
365 // Migrate acceptable ammo and ammo modifiers
366 migrate_ammo_set( obj.mod->acceptable_ammo );
367 migrate_ammo_set( obj.mod->ammo_modifier );
368
369 for( auto kv = obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.begin(); kv != obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.end(); ) {
370 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( kv->first.obj().default_ammotype() );
371 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
372 for( const itype_id &compatible_mag : kv->second ) {
373 obj.mod->magazine_adaptor[maybe_migrated->second].insert( compatible_mag );
374 }
375 kv = obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.erase( kv );
376 } else {
377 ++kv;
378 }
379 }
380 }
381
382 if( obj.gunmod && !obj.has_flag( flag_MELEE_GUNMOD ) ) {
383 for( const std::pair<const gun_mode_id, gun_modifier_data> &pr : obj.gunmod->mode_modifier ) {
384 if( pr.first == gun_mode_REACH ) {
385 obj.item_tags.insert( flag_MELEE_GUNMOD.str() );
386 break;
387 }
388 }
389 }
390
391 if( obj.gun ) {
392 // If the gun has ammo types for which the default ammo has been migrated, we need to
393 // replace those ammo types with that of the migrated ammo
394 for( auto ammo_type_it = obj.gun->ammo.begin(); ammo_type_it != obj.gun->ammo.end(); ) {
395 auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( ammo_type_it->obj().default_ammotype() );
396 if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
397 const ammotype old_ammo = *ammo_type_it;
398 // Remove the old ammotype add the migrated version
399 ammo_type_it = obj.gun->ammo.erase( ammo_type_it );
400 const ammotype &new_ammo = maybe_migrated->second;
401 obj.gun->ammo.insert( obj.gun->ammo.begin(), new_ammo );
402 // Migrate the compatible magazines
403 auto old_mag_it = obj.magazines.find( old_ammo );
404 if( old_mag_it != obj.magazines.end() ) {
405 for( const itype_id &old_mag : old_mag_it->second ) {
406 obj.magazines[new_ammo].insert( old_mag );
407 }
408 obj.magazines.erase( old_ammo );
409 }
410 // And the default magazines for each magazine type
411 auto old_default_mag_it = obj.magazine_default.find( old_ammo );
412 if( old_default_mag_it != obj.magazine_default.end() ) {
413 const itype_id &old_default_mag = old_default_mag_it->second;
414 obj.magazine_default[new_ammo] = old_default_mag;
415 obj.magazine_default.erase( old_ammo );
416 }
417 } else {
418 ++ammo_type_it;
419 }
420 }

422 // TODO: add explicit action field to gun definitions
423 const auto defmode_name = [&]() {
424 if( obj.gun->clip == 1 ) {
425 return translate_marker( "manual" ); // break-type actions
426 } else if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "pistol" ) && obj.has_flag( "RELOAD_ONE" ) ) {
427 return translate_marker( "revolver" );
428 } else {
429 return translate_marker( "semi" );
430 }
431 };
432
433 // if the gun doesn't have a DEFAULT mode then add one now
434 obj.gun->modes.emplace( gun_mode_id( "DEFAULT" ),
435 gun_modifier_data( defmode_name(), 1, std::set<std::string>() ) );
436
437 // If a "gun" has a reach attack, give it an additional melee mode.
438 if( obj.has_flag( "REACH_ATTACK" ) ) {
439 obj.gun->modes.emplace( gun_mode_id( "MELEE" ),
440 gun_modifier_data( translate_marker( "melee" ), 1,
441 { "MELEE" } ) );
442 }
443 if( obj.gun->burst > 1 ) {
444 // handle legacy JSON format
445 obj.gun->modes.emplace( gun_mode_id( "AUTO" ),
446 gun_modifier_data( translate_marker( "auto" ), obj.gun->burst,
447 std::set<std::string>() ) );
448 }

450 if( obj.gun->handling < 0 ) {
451 bool burst_only = std::all_of( obj.gun->modes.begin(), obj.gun->modes.end(),
452 []( const std::pair<gun_mode_id, gun_modifier_data> &pr ) {
453 return pr.second.qty() > 1 || pr.second.flags().count( "MELEE" ) > 0;
454 } );
455 // TODO: specify in JSON via classes
456 if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "shotgun" ) ) {
457 obj.gun->handling = 30;
458 } else if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "rifle" ) ||
459 obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "smg" ) ) {

461 } else {
462 obj.gun->handling = burst_only ? 25 : 15;

464 }

466 obj.gun->reload_noise = _( obj.gun->reload_noise );
467
468 // TODO: Move to jsons?
469 if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "archery" ) ||
470 obj.gun->skill_used == skill_id( "throw" ) ) {
471 obj.item_tags.insert( "WATERPROOF_GUN" );
472 obj.item_tags.insert( "NEVER_JAMS" );
473 obj.gun->ammo_effects.insert( ammo_effect_NEVER_MISFIRES );

477 set_allergy_flags( obj );
478 hflesh_to_flesh( obj );
479 npc_implied_flags( obj );
480
481 if( obj.comestible ) {
482 std::map<vitamin_id, int> &vitamins = obj.comestible->default_nutrition.vitamins;
483 if( get_option<bool>( "NO_VITAMINS" ) ) {
484 for( auto &vit : vitamins ) {

490 // Default vitamins of healthy comestibles to their edible base materials if none explicitly specified.

492 auto mat = obj.materials;

511 if( obj.tool ) {
512 if( !obj.tool->subtype.is_empty() && has_template( obj.tool->subtype ) ) {

518 {

575void Item_factory::register_cached_uses( const itype &obj )
576{
577 for( auto &e : obj.use_methods ) {
578 // can this item function as a repair tool?
579 if( repair_actions.count( e.first ) ) {
580 repair_tools.insert( obj.id );
581 }
582
583 // can this item be used to repair complex firearms?
584 if( e.first == "GUN_REPAIR" ) {
585 gun_tools.insert( obj.id );
586 }
587 }
588}

590void Item_factory::finalize_post( itype &obj )
591{
592 // erase all invalid flags (not defined in flags.json), display warning about invalid flags
593 erase_if( obj.item_tags, [&]( const std::string & f ) {
594 if( !json_flag::get( f ).id.is_valid() ) {
595 debugmsg( "itype '%s' uses undefined flag '%s'. Please add corresponding 'json_flag' entry to json.",
596 obj.id.c_str(), f );
597 return true;
598 } else {
599 return false;
600 }
601 } );
602
603 // handle complex firearms as a special case
604 if( obj.gun && !obj.has_flag( "PRIMITIVE_RANGED_WEAPON" ) ) {
605 std::copy( gun_tools.begin(), gun_tools.end(), std::inserter( obj.repair, obj.repair.begin() ) );
606 return;
607 }
608
609 // for each item iterate through potential repair tools
610 for( const auto &tool : repair_tools ) {
611
612 // check if item can be repaired with any of the actions?
613 for( const auto &act : repair_actions ) {
614 const use_function *func = m_templates[tool].get_use( act );
615 if( func == nullptr ) {
616 continue;
617 }
618
619 // tool has a possible repair action, check if the materials are compatible
620 const auto &opts = dynamic_cast<const repair_item_actor *>( func->get_actor_ptr() )->materials;
621 if( std::any_of( obj.materials.begin(), obj.materials.end(), [&opts]( const material_id & m ) {
622 return opts.count( m ) > 0;
623 } ) ) {
624 obj.repair.insert( tool );
625 }
626 }
627 }
628
629 if( obj.comestible ) {
630 for( const std::pair<diseasetype_id, int> elem : obj.comestible->contamination ) {
631 const diseasetype_id dtype = elem.first;
632 if( !dtype.is_valid() ) {
633 debugmsg( "contamination in %s contains invalid diseasetype_id %s.",
634 obj.id.str(), dtype.str() );
635 }
636 }
637 }
638}
639
640void Item_factory::finalize()
641{
642 DynamicDataLoader::get_instance().load_deferred( deferred );
643
644 finalize_item_blacklist();
645
646 // we can no longer add or adjust static item templates
647 frozen = true;
648
649 for( auto &e : m_templates ) {
650 finalize_pre( e.second );
651 register_cached_uses( e.second );
652 }
653
654 for( auto &e : m_templates ) {
655 finalize_post( e.second );
656 }
657
658 // We may actually have some runtimes here - ones loaded from saved game
659 // TODO: support for runtimes that repair
660 for( auto &e : m_runtimes ) {
661 finalize_pre( *e.second );
662 finalize_post( *e.second );
663 }
664
665 // for each item register all (non-obsolete) potential recipes
666 for( const std::pair<const recipe_id, recipe> &p : recipe_dict ) {
667 const recipe &rec = p.second;
668 if( rec.obsolete || rec.will_be_blacklisted() ) {
669 continue;
670 }
671 const itype_id &result = rec.result();
672 auto it = m_templates.find( result );
673 if( it != m_templates.end() ) {
674 it->second.recipes.push_back( p.first );
675 }
676 }
677}
678
679void Item_factory::finalize_item_blacklist()
680{
681 for( const itype_id &blackout : item_blacklist ) {
682 std::unordered_map<itype_id, itype>::iterator candidate = m_templates.find( blackout );
683 if( candidate == m_templates.end() ) {
684 debugmsg( "item on blacklist %s does not exist", blackout.c_str() );
685 continue;
686 }
687
688 for( std::pair<const item_group_id, std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data>> &g : m_template_groups ) {
689 g.second->remove_item( candidate->first );
690 }
691
692 // remove any blacklisted items from requirements
693 for( const std::pair<const requirement_id, requirement_data> &r : requirement_data::all() ) {
694 const_cast<requirement_data &>( r.second ).blacklist_item( candidate->first );
695 }
696
697 // remove any recipes used to craft the blacklisted item
698 recipe_dictionary::delete_if( [&candidate]( const recipe & r ) {
699 return r.result() == candidate->first;
700 } );
701 }
702 for( vproto_id &vid : vehicle_prototype::get_all() ) {
703 vehicle_prototype &prototype = const_cast<vehicle_prototype &>( vid.obj() );
704 for( vehicle_item_spawn &vis : prototype.item_spawns ) {
705 auto &vec = vis.item_ids;
706 const auto iter = std::remove_if( vec.begin(), vec.end(), item_is_blacklisted );
707 vec.erase( iter, vec.end() );
708 }
709 }
710
711 for( const std::pair<const itype_id, migration> &migrate : migrations ) {
712 if( m_templates.find( migrate.second.replace ) == m_templates.end() ) {
713 debugmsg( "Replacement item for migration %s does not exist", migrate.first.c_str() );
714 continue;
715 }
716
717 for( std::pair<const item_group_id, std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data>> &g : m_template_groups ) {
718 g.second->replace_item( migrate.first, migrate.second.replace );
719 }
720
721 // replace migrated items in requirements
722 for( const std::pair<const requirement_id, requirement_data> &r : requirement_data::all() ) {
723 const_cast<requirement_data &>( r.second ).replace_item( migrate.first,
724 migrate.second.replace );
725 }
726
727 // remove any recipes used to craft the migrated item
728 // if there's a valid recipe, it will be for the replacement
729 recipe_dictionary::delete_if( [&migrate]( const recipe & r ) {
730 return !r.obsolete && r.result() == migrate.first;
731 } );
732
733 // If the default ammo of an ammo_type gets migrated, we migrate all guns using that ammo
734 // type to the ammo type of whatever that default ammo was migrated to.
735 // To do that we need to store a map of ammo to the migration replacement thereof.
736 auto maybe_ammo = m_templates.find( migrate.first );
737 // If the itype_id is valid and the itype has ammo data
738 if( maybe_ammo != m_templates.end() && maybe_ammo->second.ammo ) {
739 auto replacement = m_templates.find( migrate.second.replace );
740 if( replacement->second.ammo ) {
741 migrated_ammo.emplace( std::make_pair( migrate.first, replacement->second.ammo->type ) );
742 } else {
743 debugmsg( "Replacement item %s for migrated ammo %s is not ammo.",
744 migrate.second.replace.str(), migrate.first.str() );
745 }
746 }
747
748 // migrate magazines as well
749 auto maybe_mag = m_templates.find( migrate.first );
750 if( maybe_mag != m_templates.end() && maybe_mag->second.magazine ) {
751 auto replacement = m_templates.find( migrate.second.replace );
752 if( replacement->second.magazine ) {
753 migrated_magazines.emplace( std::make_pair( migrate.first, migrate.second.replace ) );
754 } else {
755 debugmsg( "Replacement item %s for migrated magazine %s is not a magazine.",
756 migrate.second.replace.str(), migrate.first.str() );
757 }
758 }
759 }
760 for( vproto_id &vid : vehicle_prototype::get_all() ) {
761 vehicle_prototype &prototype = const_cast<vehicle_prototype &>( vid.obj() );
762 for( vehicle_item_spawn &vis : prototype.item_spawns ) {
763 for( itype_id &type_to_spawn : vis.item_ids ) {
764 std::map<itype_id, migration>::iterator replacement =
765 migrations.find( type_to_spawn );
766 if( replacement != migrations.end() ) {
767 type_to_spawn = replacement->second.replace;
768 }
769 }
770 }
771 }
772}

786class iuse_function_wrapper : public iuse_actor
787{
788 private:
789 use_function_pointer cpp_function;
790 public:
791 iuse_function_wrapper( const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f )
792 : iuse_actor( type ), cpp_function( f ) { }
793
794 ~iuse_function_wrapper() override = default;
795 int use( player &p, item &it, bool a, const tripoint &pos ) const override {
796 return ( *cpp_function )( &p, &it, a, pos );
797 }
798 std::unique_ptr<iuse_actor> clone() const override {
799 return std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper>( *this );
800 }
801
802 void load( const JsonObject & ) override {}
803};
804
805class iuse_function_wrapper_with_info : public iuse_function_wrapper
806{
807 private:
808 std::string info_string; // Untranslated
809 public:
810 iuse_function_wrapper_with_info(
811 const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f, const std::string &info )
812 : iuse_function_wrapper( type, f ), info_string( info ) { }
813
814 void info( const item &, std::vector<iteminfo> &info ) const override {
815 info.emplace_back( "DESCRIPTION", _( info_string ) );
816 }
817 std::unique_ptr<iuse_actor> clone() const override {
818 return std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper_with_info>( *this );
819 }
820};
821
822use_function::use_function( const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f )
823 : use_function( std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper>( type, f ) ) {}
824
825void Item_factory::add_iuse( const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f )
826{
827 iuse_function_list[ type ] = use_function( type, f );
828}
829
830void Item_factory::add_iuse( const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f,
831 const std::string &info )
832{
833 iuse_function_list[ type ] =
834 use_function( std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper_with_info>( type, f, info ) );
835}
836
837void Item_factory::add_actor( std::unique_ptr<iuse_actor> ptr )
838{
839 std::string type = ptr->type;
840 iuse_function_list[ type ] = use_function( std::move( ptr ) );
841}
842
843void Item_factory::add_item_type( const itype &def )
844{
845 if( m_runtimes.count( def.id ) > 0 ) {
846 // Do NOT allow overwriting it, it's undefined behavior
847 debugmsg( "Tried to add runtime type %s, but it exists already", def.id.c_str() );
848 return;
849 }
850
851 auto &new_item_ptr = m_runtimes[ def.id ];
852 new_item_ptr = std::make_unique<itype>( def );
853 if( frozen ) {
854 finalize_pre( *new_item_ptr );
855 finalize_post( *new_item_ptr );
856 }
857}

1102
1103bool Item_factory::check_ammo_type( std::string &msg, const ammotype &ammo ) const
1104{
1105 if( ammo.is_null() ) {
1106 return false;
1107 }
1108
1109 if( !ammo.is_valid() ) {
1110 msg += string_format( "ammo type %s is not known\n", ammo.c_str() );
1111 return false;
1112 }
1113
1114 if( std::none_of( m_templates.begin(),
1115 m_templates.end(), [&ammo]( const decltype( m_templates )::value_type & e ) {
1116 return e.second.ammo && e.second.ammo->type == ammo;
1117} ) ) {
1118 msg += string_format( "there is no actual ammo of type %s defined\n", ammo.c_str() );
1119 return false;
1120 }
1121 return true;
1122}
1123
1124void Item_factory::check_definitions() const
1125{
1126 for( const auto &elem : m_templates ) {
1127 std::string msg;
1128 const itype *type = &elem.second;
1129
1130 if( !type->category_force.is_valid() ) {
1131 msg += "undefined category " + type->category_force.str() + "\n";
1132 }
1133
1134 if( type->weight < 0_gram ) {
1135 msg += "negative weight\n";
1136 }
1137 if( type->volume < 0_ml ) {
1138 msg += "negative volume\n";
1139 }
1140 if( type->count_by_charges() || type->phase == LIQUID ) {
1141 if( type->stack_size <= 0 ) {
1142 msg += string_format( "invalid stack_size %d on type using charges\n", type->stack_size );
1143 }
1144 }
1145 if( type->price < 0_cent ) {
1146 msg += "negative price\n";
1147 }
1148 if( type->damage_min() > 0 || type->damage_max() < 0 || type->damage_min() > type->damage_max() ) {
1149 msg += "invalid damage range\n";
1150 }
1151 if( type->description.empty() ) {
1152 msg += "empty description\n";
1153 }
1154
1155 for( const material_id &mat_id : type->materials ) {
1156 if( mat_id.str() == "null" || !mat_id.is_valid() ) {
1157 msg += string_format( "invalid material %s\n", mat_id.c_str() );
1158 }
1159 }
1160
1161 if( type->sym.empty() ) {
1162 msg += "symbol not defined\n";
1163 } else if( utf8_width( type->sym ) != 1 ) {
1164 msg += "symbol must be exactly one console cell width\n";
1165 }
1166
1167 for( const auto &_a : type->techniques ) {
1168 if( !_a.is_valid() ) {
1169 msg += string_format( "unknown technique %s\n", _a.c_str() );
1170 }
1171 }
1172 if( !type->snippet_category.empty() ) {
1173 if( !SNIPPET.has_category( type->snippet_category ) ) {
1174 msg += string_format( "item %s: snippet category %s without any snippets\n", type->id.c_str(),
1175 type->snippet_category.c_str() );
1176 }
1177 }
1178 for( auto &q : type->qualities ) {
1179 if( !q.first.is_valid() ) {
1180 msg += string_format( "item %s has unknown quality %s\n", type->id.c_str(), q.first.c_str() );
1181 }
1182 }
1183 if( type->default_container && !has_template( *type->default_container ) ) {
1184 if( !type->default_container->is_null() ) {
1185 msg += string_format( "invalid container property %s\n", type->default_container->c_str() );
1186 }
1187 }
1188
1189 for( const auto &e : type->emits ) {
1190 if( !e.is_valid() ) {
1191 msg += string_format( "item %s has unknown emit source %s\n", type->id.c_str(), e.c_str() );
1192 }
1193 }
1194
1195 for( const auto &f : type->faults ) {
1196 if( !f.is_valid() ) {
1197 msg += string_format( "invalid item fault %s\n", f.c_str() );
1198 }
1199 }
1200
1201 if( type->has_flag( "FIRESTARTER" ) &&
1202 !type->can_have_charges() &&
1203 !type->get_use( "firestarter" ) ) {
1204 msg += string_format( "has 'FIRESTARTER' flag, but neither can have charges nor defines 'firestarter' use func" );
1205 }
1206
1207 if( type->comestible ) {
1208 if( !type->comestible->tool.is_null() ) {
1209 auto req_tool = find_template( type->comestible->tool );
1210 if( !req_tool->tool ) {
1211 msg += string_format( "invalid tool property %s\n", type->comestible->tool.c_str() );
1212 }
1213 }
1214 }
1215 if( type->brewable ) {
1216 if( type->brewable->time < 1_turns ) {
1217 msg += "brewable time is less than 1 turn\n";
1218 }
1219
1220 if( type->brewable->results.empty() ) {
1221 msg += "empty product list\n";
1222 }
1223
1224 for( auto &b : type->brewable->results ) {
1225 if( !has_template( b ) ) {
1226 msg += string_format( "invalid result id %s\n", b.c_str() );
1227 }
1228 }
1229 }
1230 if( type->seed ) {
1231 if( type->seed->grow < 1_turns ) {
1232 msg += "seed growing time is less than 1 turn\n";
1233 }
1234 if( !has_template( type->seed->fruit_id ) ) {
1235 msg += string_format( "invalid fruit id %s\n", type->seed->fruit_id.c_str() );
1236 }
1237 for( auto &b : type->seed->byproducts ) {
1238 if( !has_template( b ) ) {
1239 msg += string_format( "invalid byproduct id %s\n", b.c_str() );
1240 }
1241 }
1242 }
1243 if( type->book ) {
1244 if( type->book->skill && !type->book->skill.is_valid() ) {
1245 msg += "uses invalid book skill.\n";
1246 }
1247 if( type->book->martial_art && !type->book->martial_art.is_valid() ) {
1248 msg += string_format( "trains invalid martial art '%s'.\n", type->book->martial_art.str() );
1249 }
1250 if( type->can_use( "MA_MANUAL" ) && !type->book->martial_art ) {
1251 msg += "has use_action MA_MANUAL but does not specify a martial art\n";
1252 }
1253 }
1254 if( type->can_use( "MA_MANUAL" ) && !type->book ) {
1255 msg += "has use_action MA_MANUAL but is not a book\n";
1256 }
1257 if( type->milling_data ) {
1258 if( !has_template( type->milling_data->into_ ) ) {
1259 msg += "type to mill into is invalid: " + type->milling_data->into_.str() + "\n";
1260 }
1261 }
1262 if( type->ammo ) {
1263 if( !type->ammo->type && type->ammo->type != ammotype( "NULL" ) ) {
1264 msg += "must define at least one ammo type\n";
1265 }
1266 check_ammo_type( msg, type->ammo->type );
1267 if( type->ammo->casing && ( !has_template( *type->ammo->casing ) ||
1268 type->ammo->casing->is_null() ) ) {
1269 msg += string_format( "invalid casing property %s\n", type->ammo->casing->c_str() );
1270 }
1271 if( !type->ammo->drop.is_null() && !has_template( type->ammo->drop ) ) {
1272 msg += string_format( "invalid drop item %s\n", type->ammo->drop.c_str() );
1273 }
1274 if( type->ammo->range != 0 && type->ammo->shape ) {
1275 msg += string_format( "shape is set, but range is %d != 0", type->ammo->range );
1276 }
1277 }
1278 if( type->battery ) {
1279 if( type->battery->max_capacity < 0_J ) {
1280 msg += "battery cannot have negative maximum charge\n";
1281 }
1282 }
1283 if( type->gun ) {
1284 for( const ammotype &at : type->gun->ammo ) {
1285 check_ammo_type( msg, at );
1286 }
1287 if( type->gun->ammo.empty() ) {
1288 // if gun doesn't use ammo forbid both integral or detachable magazines
1289 if( static_cast<bool>( type->gun->clip ) || !type->magazines.empty() ) {
1290 msg += "cannot specify clip_size or magazine without ammo type\n";
1291 }
1292
1293 if( type->has_flag( "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT" ) ) {
1294 msg += "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT requires an ammo type to be specified\n";
1295 }
1296
1297 } else {
1298 if( type->has_flag( "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT" ) && !type->magazines.empty() ) {
1299 msg += "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT cannot be used with magazines\n";
1300 }
1301 for( const ammotype &at : type->gun->ammo ) {
1302 if( !type->gun->clip && !type->magazines.empty() && !type->magazine_default.count( at ) ) {
1303 msg += string_format( "specified magazine but none provided for ammo type %s\n", at.str() );
1304 }
1305 }
1306 }
1307 if( type->gun->barrel_length < 0_ml ) {
1308 msg += "gun barrel length cannot be negative\n";
1309 }
1310
1311 if( !type->gun->skill_used ) {
1312 msg += "uses no skill\n";
1313 } else if( !type->gun->skill_used.is_valid() ) {
1314 msg += string_format( "uses an invalid skill %s\n", type->gun->skill_used.str() );
1315 }
1316 for( auto &gm : type->gun->default_mods ) {
1317 if( !has_template( gm ) ) {
1318 msg += "invalid default mod.\n";
1319 }
1320 }
1321 for( auto &gm : type->gun->built_in_mods ) {
1322 if( !has_template( gm ) ) {
1323 msg += "invalid built-in mod.\n";
1324 }
1325 }
1326 }
1327 if( type->gunmod ) {
1328 if( type->gunmod->location.str().empty() ) {
1329 msg += "gunmod does not specify location\n";
1330 }
1331 if( ( type->gunmod->sight_dispersion < 0 ) != ( type->gunmod->aim_speed < 0 ) ) {
1332 msg += "gunmod must have both sight_dispersion and aim_speed set or neither of them set\n";
1333 }
1334 for( const gun_type_type &t : type->gunmod->usable ) {
1335 // TODO: Make gun_type_type not require horrid checks like this one
1336 const skill_id gun_skill = skill_id( t.name_ );
1337 bool is_skill = ( gun_skill.is_valid() && gun_skill->is_combat_skill() )
1338 || t.name_ == "bow"
1339 || t.name_ == "crossbow";
1340 itype_id item_type( t.name_ );
1341 bool is_item = item_type.is_valid();
1342 if( !is_skill && !is_item ) {
1343 msg += string_format( "gunmod is usable for invalid item/gun type %s\n", t.name_ );
1344 continue;
1345 }
1346
1347 if( json_report_strict && t.name_ == "bow" ) {
1348 msg += string_format( "'bow' location is deprecated, use 'archery' instead" );
1349 }
1350
1351 // We need to check is_skill because something can be both an item and a skill
1352 if( !is_skill && is_item ) {
1353 const itype *target = &*item_type;
1354 if( target->gun->valid_mod_locations.count( type->gunmod->location ) == 0 ) {
1355 msg += string_format( "gunmod is usable for gun %s which doesn't have a slot of type %s\n",
1356 t.name_, type->gunmod->location.str() );
1357 }
1358
1359 if( type->mod != nullptr && !type->mod->ammo_modifier.empty() ) {
1360 auto acceptable_ammo = type->mod->ammo_modifier;
1361 for( const auto &pr : type->mod->magazine_adaptor ) {
1362 acceptable_ammo.insert( pr.first );
1363 }
1364 auto acceptable_magazines = !type->mod->magazine_adaptor.empty()
1365 ? type->mod->magazine_adaptor
1366 : target->magazines;
1367 for( const ammotype &ammo : acceptable_ammo ) {
1368 if( acceptable_magazines.find( ammo ) == acceptable_magazines.end() ) {
1369 msg += string_format( "gunmod can be applied to %s, which has no magazines for ammo %s\n",
1370 t.name_, ammo.str() );
1371 }
1372 }
1373 }
1374 }
1375 }
1376 }
1377 if( type->mod ) {
1378 for( const ammotype &at : type->mod->ammo_modifier ) {
1379 check_ammo_type( msg, at );
1380 }
1381
1382 for( const auto &e : type->mod->acceptable_ammo ) {
1383 check_ammo_type( msg, e );
1384 }
1385
1386 for( const auto &e : type->mod->magazine_adaptor ) {
1387 check_ammo_type( msg, e.first );
1388 if( e.second.empty() ) {
1389 msg += string_format( "no magazines specified for ammo type %s\n", e.first.str() );
1390 }
1391 for( const itype_id &opt : e.second ) {
1392 const itype *mag = find_template( opt );
1393 if( !mag->magazine || !mag->magazine->type.count( e.first ) ) {
1394 msg += string_format( "invalid magazine %s in magazine adapter\n", opt.str() );
1395 }
1396 }
1397 }
1398 }
1399 if( type->magazine ) {
1400 for( const ammotype &at : type->magazine->type ) {
1401 check_ammo_type( msg, at );
1402 }
1403 if( type->magazine->type.empty() ) {
1404 msg += "magazine did not specify ammo type\n";
1405 }
1406 if( type->magazine->capacity < 0 ) {
1407 msg += string_format( "invalid capacity %i\n", type->magazine->capacity );
1408 }
1409 if( type->magazine->count < 0 || type->magazine->count > type->magazine->capacity ) {
1410 msg += string_format( "invalid count %i\n", type->magazine->count );
1411 }
1412 const itype *da = find_template( type->magazine->default_ammo );
1413 if( !( da->ammo && type->magazine->type.count( da->ammo->type ) ) ) {
1414 msg += string_format( "invalid default_ammo %s\n", type->magazine->default_ammo.str() );
1415 }
1416 if( type->magazine->reliability < 0 || type->magazine->reliability > 100 ) {
1417 msg += string_format( "invalid reliability %i\n", type->magazine->reliability );
1418 }
1419 if( type->magazine->reload_time < 0 ) {
1420 msg += string_format( "invalid reload_time %i\n", type->magazine->reload_time );
1421 }
1422 if( type->magazine->linkage && ( !has_template( *type->magazine->linkage ) ||
1423 type->magazine->linkage->is_null() ) ) {
1424 msg += string_format( "invalid linkage property %s\n", type->magazine->linkage->c_str() );
1425 }
1426 }
1427
1428 for( const std::pair<const string_id<ammunition_type>, std::set<itype_id>> &ammo_variety :
1429 type->magazines ) {
1430 if( ammo_variety.second.empty() ) {
1431 msg += string_format( "no magazine specified for %s\n", ammo_variety.first.str() );
1432 }
1433 for( const itype_id &magazine : ammo_variety.second ) {
1434 const itype *mag_ptr = find_template( magazine );
1435 if( mag_ptr == nullptr ) {
1436 msg += string_format( "magazine \"%s\" specified for \"%s\" does not exist\n",
1437 magazine.str(), ammo_variety.first.str() );
1438 } else if( !mag_ptr->magazine ) {
1439 msg += string_format(
1440 "magazine \"%s\" specified for \"%s\" is not a magazine\n", magazine.str(),
1441 ammo_variety.first.str() );
1442 } else if( !mag_ptr->magazine->type.count( ammo_variety.first ) ) {
1443 msg += string_format( "magazine \"%s\" does not take compatible ammo\n", magazine );
1444 } else if( mag_ptr->has_flag( "SPEEDLOADER" ) &&
1445 mag_ptr->magazine->capacity != type->gun->clip ) {
1446 msg += string_format(
1447 "speedloader %s capacity (%d) does not match gun capacity (%d).\n",
1448 magazine.str(), mag_ptr->magazine->capacity, type->gun->clip );
1449 }
1450 }
1451 }
1452
1453 if( type->tool ) {
1454 for( const ammotype &at : type->tool->ammo_id ) {
1455 check_ammo_type( msg, at );
1456 }
1457 if( type->tool->revert_to && ( !has_template( *type->tool->revert_to ) ||
1458 type->tool->revert_to->is_null() ) ) {
1459 msg += string_format( "invalid revert_to property %s\n", type->tool->revert_to->c_str() );
1460 }
1461 if( !type->tool->revert_msg.empty() && !type->tool->revert_to ) {
1462 msg += "cannot specify revert_msg without revert_to\n";
1463 }
1464 if( !type->tool->subtype.is_empty() && !has_template( type->tool->subtype ) ) {
1465 msg += string_format( "invalid tool subtype %s\n", type->tool->subtype.str() );
1466 }
1467 }
1468 if( type->bionic ) {
1469 if( !type->bionic->id.is_valid() ) {
1470 msg += string_format( "there is no bionic with id %s\n", type->bionic->id.c_str() );
1471 }
1472 }
1473
1474 if( type->container ) {
1475 if( type->container->seals && !type->container->unseals_into.is_null() ) {
1476 msg += string_format( "resealable container unseals_into %s\n",
1477 type->container->unseals_into.c_str() );
1478 }
1479 if( type->container->contains <= 0_ml ) {
1480 msg += string_format( "\"contains\" (%d) must be >0\n", type->container->contains.value() );
1481 }
1482 if( !has_template( type->container->unseals_into ) ) {
1483 msg += string_format( "unseals_into invalid id %s\n", type->container->unseals_into.c_str() );
1484 }
1485 }
1486
1487 if( type->relic_data ) {
1488 type->relic_data->check();
1489 }
1490
1491 for( const auto &elem : type->use_methods ) {
1492 const iuse_actor *actor = elem.second.get_actor_ptr();
1493
1494 assert( actor );
1495 if( !actor->is_valid() ) {
1496 msg += string_format( "item action \"%s\" was not described.\n", actor->type.c_str() );
1497 }
1498
1499 if( actor->type == "CABLE_ATTACH" && !vpart_id( type->id.str() ).is_valid() ) {
1500 msg += string_format( "no valid vehicle part for CABLE_ATTACH action\n" );
1501 }
1502 }
1503
1504 if( type->fuel && !type->count_by_charges() ) {
1505 msg += "fuel value set, but item isn't count_by_charges.\n";
1506 }
1507
1508 if( msg.empty() ) {
1509 continue;
1510 }
1511 debugmsg( "warnings for type %s:\n%s", type->id.c_str(), msg );
1512 }
1513 for( const auto &e : migrations ) {
1514 if( !m_templates.count( e.second.replace ) ) {
1515 debugmsg( "Invalid migration target: %s", e.second.replace.c_str() );
1516 }
1517 for( const auto &c : e.second.contents ) {
1518 if( !m_templates.count( c ) ) {
1519 debugmsg( "Invalid migration contents: %s", c.c_str() );
1520 }
1521 }
1522 }
1523 for( const auto &elem : m_template_groups ) {
1524 elem.second->check_consistency( elem.first.str() );
1525 }
1526}
1527
1528//Returns the template with the given identification tag
1529const itype *Item_factory::find_template( const itype_id &id ) const
1530{
1531 assert( frozen );
1532
1533 auto found = m_templates.find( id );
1534 if( found != m_templates.end() ) {
1535 return &found->second;
1536 }
1537
1538 auto rt = m_runtimes.find( id );
1539 if( rt != m_runtimes.end() ) {
1540 return rt->second.get();
1541 }
1542
1543 //If we didn't find the item maybe it is a building instead!
1544 const recipe_id &making_id = recipe_id( id.c_str() );
1545 if( oter_str_id( id.c_str() ).is_valid() ||
1546 ( making_id.is_valid() && making_id.obj().is_blueprint() ) ) {
1547 itype *def = new itype();
1548 def->id = id;
1549 def->name = no_translation( string_format( "DEBUG: %s", id.c_str() ) );
1550 def->description = making_id.obj().description;
1551 m_runtimes[ id ].reset( def );
1552 return def;
1553 }
1554
1555 debugmsg( "Missing item definition: %s", id.c_str() );
1556
1557 itype *def = new itype();
1558 def->id = id;
1559 def->name = no_translation( string_format( "undefined-%s", id.c_str() ) );
1560 def->description = no_translation( string_format( "Missing item definition for %s.", id.c_str() ) );
1561
1562 m_runtimes[ id ].reset( def );
1563 return def;
1564}
1565
1566Item_spawn_data *Item_factory::get_group( const item_group_id &item_group_id )
1567{
1568 GroupMap::iterator group_iter = m_template_groups.find( item_group_id );
1569 if( group_iter != m_template_groups.end() ) {
1570 return group_iter->second.get();
1571 }
1572 return nullptr;
1573}

1578
1579template<typename SlotType>
1580void Item_factory::load_slot( cata::value_ptr<SlotType> &slotptr, const JsonObject &jo,
1581 const std::string &src )
1582{
1583 if( !slotptr ) {
1584 slotptr = cata::make_value<SlotType>();
1585 }
1586 load( *slotptr, jo, src );
1587}
1588
1589template<typename SlotType>
1590void Item_factory::load_slot_optional( cata::value_ptr<SlotType> &slotptr, const JsonObject &jo,
1591 const std::string &member, const std::string &src )
1592{
1593 if( !jo.has_member( member ) ) {
1594 return;
1595 }
1596 JsonObject slotjo = jo.get_object( member );
1597 load_slot( slotptr, slotjo, src );
1598}
1599
1600template<typename E>
1601void load_optional_enum_array( std::vector<E> &vec, const JsonObject &jo,
1602 const std::string &member )
1603{
1604
1605 if( !jo.has_member( member ) ) {
1606 return;
1607 } else if( !jo.has_array( member ) ) {
1608 jo.throw_error( "expected array", member );
1609 }
1610
1611 JsonIn &stream = *jo.get_raw( member );
1612 stream.start_array();
1613 while( !stream.end_array() ) {
1614 vec.push_back( stream.get_enum_value<E>() );
1615 }
1616}
1617
1618bool Item_factory::load_definition( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &src, itype &def )
1619{
1620 assert( !frozen );
1621
1622 if( !jo.has_string( "copy-from" ) ) {
1623 // if this is a new definition ensure we start with a clean itype
1624 def = itype();
1625 return true;
1626 }
1627
1628 itype_id copy_from;
1629 jo.read( "copy-from", copy_from, true );
1630 auto base = m_templates.find( copy_from );
1631 if( base != m_templates.end() ) {
1632 def = base->second;
1633 def.looks_like = copy_from;
1634 def.was_loaded = true;
1635 return true;
1636 }
1637
1638 auto abstract = m_abstracts.find( copy_from );
1639 if( abstract != m_abstracts.end() ) {
1640 def = abstract->second;
1641 if( def.looks_like.is_empty() ) {
1642 def.looks_like = copy_from;
1643 }
1644 def.was_loaded = true;
1645 return true;
1646 }
1647
1648 deferred.emplace_back( jo.get_source_location(), src );
1649 jo.allow_omitted_members();
1650 return false;
1651}

1895 }

1920 "rand_charges" );

2019void Item_factory::load( islot_comestible &slot, const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &src )
2020{
2021 bool strict = src == "dda";
2022
2023 JsonObject relative = jo.get_object( "relative" );
2024 JsonObject proportional = jo.get_object( "proportional" );
2025 relative.allow_omitted_members();
2026 proportional.allow_omitted_members();
2027
2028 assign( jo, "comestible_type", slot.comesttype, strict );
2029 assign( jo, "tool", slot.tool, strict );
2030 assign( jo, "charges", slot.def_charges, strict, 1 );
2031 assign( jo, "quench", slot.quench, strict );
2032 assign( jo, "fun", slot.fun, strict );
2033 assign( jo, "stim", slot.stim, strict );
2034 assign( jo, "fatigue_mod", slot.fatigue_mod, strict );
2035 assign( jo, "healthy", slot.healthy, strict );
2036 assign( jo, "parasites", slot.parasites, strict, 0 );
2037 assign( jo, "radiation", slot.radiation, strict );
2038 assign( jo, "freezing_point", slot.freeze_point, strict );
2039 assign( jo, "spoils_in", slot.spoils, strict, 1_hours );
2040 assign( jo, "cooks_like", slot.cooks_like, strict );
2041 assign( jo, "smoking_result", slot.smoking_result, strict );
2042
2043 for( const JsonObject &jsobj : jo.get_array( "contamination" ) ) {
2044 slot.contamination.emplace( diseasetype_id( jsobj.get_string( "disease" ) ),
2045 jsobj.get_int( "probability" ) );
2046 }
2047
2048 if( jo.has_member( "primary_material" ) ) {
2049 std::string mat = jo.get_string( "primary_material" );
2050 slot.specific_heat_solid = material_id( mat )->specific_heat_solid();
2051 slot.specific_heat_liquid = material_id( mat )->specific_heat_liquid();
2052 slot.latent_heat = material_id( mat )->latent_heat();
2053 } else if( jo.has_member( "material" ) ) {
2054 float specific_heat_solid = 0;
2055 float specific_heat_liquid = 0;
2056 float latent_heat = 0;
2057
2058 for( const std::string &m : jo.get_tags( "material" ) ) {
2059 specific_heat_solid += material_id( m )->specific_heat_solid();
2060 specific_heat_liquid += material_id( m )->specific_heat_liquid();
2061 latent_heat += material_id( m )->latent_heat();
2062 }
2063 // Average based on number of materials.
2064 slot.specific_heat_liquid = specific_heat_liquid / jo.get_tags( "material" ).size();
2065 slot.specific_heat_solid = specific_heat_solid / jo.get_tags( "material" ).size();
2066 slot.latent_heat = latent_heat / jo.get_tags( "material" ).size();
2067 }
2068
2069 bool is_not_boring = false;
2070 if( jo.has_member( "primary_material" ) ) {
2071 std::string mat = jo.get_string( "primary_material" );
2072 is_not_boring = is_not_boring || mat == "junk";
2073 }
2074 if( jo.has_member( "material" ) ) {
2075 for( const std::string &m : jo.get_tags( "material" ) ) {
2076 is_not_boring = is_not_boring || m == "junk";
2077 }
2078 }
2079 // Junk food never gets old by default, but this can still be overridden.
2080 if( is_not_boring ) {
2081 slot.monotony_penalty = 0;
2082 }
2083 assign( jo, "monotony_penalty", slot.monotony_penalty, strict );
2084
2085 if( jo.has_string( "addiction_type" ) ) {
2086 slot.add = addiction_type( jo.get_string( "addiction_type" ) );
2087 }
2088
2089 assign( jo, "addiction_potential", slot.addict, strict );
2090
2091 bool got_calories = false;
2092
2093 if( jo.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
2094 slot.default_nutrition.kcal = jo.get_int( "calories" );
2095 got_calories = true;
2096
2097 } else if( relative.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
2098 slot.default_nutrition.kcal += relative.get_int( "calories" );
2099 got_calories = true;
2100
2101 } else if( proportional.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
2102 slot.default_nutrition.kcal *= proportional.get_float( "calories" );
2103 got_calories = true;
2104
2105 } else if( jo.has_member( "nutrition" ) ) {
2106 slot.default_nutrition.kcal = jo.get_int( "nutrition" ) * islot_comestible::kcal_per_nutr;
2107 }
2108
2109 if( jo.has_member( "nutrition" ) && got_calories ) {
2110 jo.throw_error( "cannot specify both nutrition and calories", "nutrition" );
2111 }
2112
2113 // any specification of vitamins suppresses use of material defaults @see Item_factory::finalize
2114 if( jo.has_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
2115 for( JsonArray pair : jo.get_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
2116 vitamin_id vit( pair.get_string( 0 ) );
2117 slot.default_nutrition.vitamins[ vit ] = pair.get_int( 1 );
2118 }
2119
2120 } else {
2121 if( relative.has_int( "vitamins" ) ) {
2122 // allows easy specification of 'fortified' comestibles
2123 for( auto &v : vitamin::all() ) {
2124 slot.default_nutrition.vitamins[ v.first ] += relative.get_int( "vitamins" );
2125 }
2126 } else if( relative.has_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
2127 for( JsonArray pair : relative.get_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
2128 vitamin_id vit( pair.get_string( 0 ) );
2129 slot.default_nutrition.vitamins[ vit ] += pair.get_int( 1 );
2130 }
2131 }
2132 }
2133
2134 if( jo.has_string( "rot_spawn" ) ) {
2135 slot.rot_spawn = mongroup_id( jo.get_string( "rot_spawn" ) );
2136 }
2137 assign( jo, "rot_spawn_chance", slot.rot_spawn_chance, strict, 0 );
2138

2320void Item_factory::set_allergy_flags( itype &item_template )
2321{
2322 using material_allergy_pair = std::pair<material_id, std::string>;

2324 // First allergens:
2325 // An item is an allergen even if it has trace amounts of allergenic material
2326 std::make_pair( material_id( "hflesh" ), "CANNIBALISM" ),
2327
2328 std::make_pair( material_id( "hflesh" ), "ALLERGEN_MEAT" ),
2329 std::make_pair( material_id( "iflesh" ), "ALLERGEN_MEAT" ),
2330 std::make_pair( material_id( "flesh" ), "ALLERGEN_MEAT" ),

2332 std::make_pair( material_id( "fruit" ), "ALLERGEN_FRUIT" ),
2333 std::make_pair( material_id( "veggy" ), "ALLERGEN_VEGGY" ),
2334 std::make_pair( material_id( "bean" ), "ALLERGEN_VEGGY" ),
2335 std::make_pair( material_id( "tomato" ), "ALLERGEN_VEGGY" ),
2336 std::make_pair( material_id( "garlic" ), "ALLERGEN_VEGGY" ),
2337 std::make_pair( material_id( "nut" ), "ALLERGEN_NUT" ),

2362// Migration helper: turns human flesh into generic flesh
2363// Don't call before making sure that the cannibalism flag is set
2364void hflesh_to_flesh( itype &item_template )
2365{
2366 auto &mats = item_template.materials;
2367 const auto old_size = mats.size();
2368 mats.erase( std::remove( mats.begin(), mats.end(), material_id( "hflesh" ) ), mats.end() );
2369 // Only add "flesh" material if not already present
2370 if( old_size != mats.size() &&
2371 std::find( mats.begin(), mats.end(), material_id( "flesh" ) ) == mats.end() ) {
2372 mats.push_back( material_id( "flesh" ) );
2373 }
2374}

2654void Item_factory::load_migration( const JsonObject &jo )
2655{
2656 migration m;
2657 assign( jo, "replace", m.replace );
2658 assign( jo, "flags", m.flags );
2659 assign( jo, "charges", m.charges );
2660 assign( jo, "contents", m.contents );
2661
2662 if( jo.has_string( "id" ) ) {
2663 jo.read( "id", m.id, true );
2664 migrations[ m.id ] = m;
2665 } else if( jo.has_array( "id" ) ) {
2666 std::vector<itype_id> ids;
2667 jo.read( "id", ids, true );
2668 for( const itype_id id : ids ) {
2669 m.id = id;
2670 migrations[ m.id ] = m;
2671 }
2672 } else {
2673 jo.throw_error( "`id` of `MIGRATION` is neither string nor array" );
2674 }
2675}

2679 auto iter = migrations.find( id );
2680 return iter != migrations.end() ? iter->second.replace : id;

2683void Item_factory::migrate_item( const itype_id &id, item &obj )
2684{
2685 auto iter = migrations.find( id );
2686 if( iter != migrations.end() ) {
2687 for( const std::string &f : iter->second.flags ) {
2688 obj.set_flag( f );
2689 }
2690 if( iter->second.charges > 0 ) {
2691 obj.charges = iter->second.charges;
2692 }
2693
2694 obj.contents.migrate_item( obj, iter->second.contents );
2695
2696 // check contents of migrated containers do not exceed capacity
2697 if( obj.is_container() && !obj.contents.empty() ) {
2698 item &child = obj.contents.back();
2699 const int capacity = child.charges_per_volume( obj.get_container_capacity() );
2700 child.charges = std::min( child.charges, capacity );
2701 }
2702 }
2703}

2812template<typename T>
2813bool load_min_max( std::pair<T, T> &pa, const JsonObject &obj, const std::string &name )
2814{
2815 bool result = false;
2816 if( obj.has_array( name ) ) {
2817 // An array means first is min, second entry is max. Both are mandatory.
2818 JsonArray arr = obj.get_array( name );
2819 result |= arr.read_next( pa.first );
2820 result |= arr.read_next( pa.second );
2821 } else {
2822 // Not an array, should be a single numeric value, which is set as min and max.
2823 result |= obj.read( name, pa.first );
2824 result |= obj.read( name, pa.second );
2825 }
2826 result |= obj.read( name + "-min", pa.first );
2827 result |= obj.read( name + "-max", pa.second );
2828 return result;
2829}
2830
2831bool Item_factory::load_sub_ref( std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data> &ptr, const JsonObject &obj,
2832 const std::string &name, const Item_group &parent )
2833{
2834 const std::string iname( name + "-item" );
2835 const std::string gname( name + "-group" );
2836 std::vector< std::pair<const std::string, bool> >
2837 entries; // pair.second is true for groups, false for items
2838 const int prob = 100;
2839
2840 auto get_array = [&obj, &name, &entries]( const std::string & arr_name, const bool isgroup ) {
2841 if( !obj.has_array( arr_name ) ) {
2842 return;
2843 } else if( name != "contents" ) {
2844 obj.throw_error( string_format( "You can't use an array for '%s'", arr_name ) );
2845 }
2846 for( const std::string line : obj.get_array( arr_name ) ) {
2847 entries.emplace_back( line, isgroup );
2848 }
2849 };
2850 get_array( iname, false );
2851 get_array( gname, true );
2852
2853 if( obj.has_member( name ) ) {
2854 obj.throw_error( string_format( "This has been a TODO: since 2014. Use '%s' and/or '%s' instead.",
2855 iname, gname ) );
2856 // TODO: !
2857 return false;
2858 }
2859 if( obj.has_string( iname ) ) {
2860 entries.push_back( std::make_pair( obj.get_string( iname ), false ) );
2861 }
2862 if( obj.has_string( gname ) ) {
2863 entries.push_back( std::make_pair( obj.get_string( gname ), true ) );
2864 }
2865
2866 if( entries.size() > 1 && name != "contents" ) {
2867 obj.throw_error( string_format( "You can only use one of '%s' and '%s'", iname, gname ) );
2868 return false;
2869 } else if( entries.size() == 1 ) {
2870 const auto type = entries.front().second ? Single_item_creator::Type::S_ITEM_GROUP :
2871 Single_item_creator::Type::S_ITEM;
2872 Single_item_creator *result = new Single_item_creator( entries.front().first, type, prob );
2873 result->inherit_ammo_mag_chances( parent.with_ammo, parent.with_magazine );
2874 ptr.reset( result );
2875 return true;
2876 } else if( entries.empty() ) {
2877 return false;
2878 }
2879 Item_group *result = new Item_group( Item_group::Type::G_COLLECTION, prob, parent.with_ammo,
2880 parent.with_magazine );
2881 ptr.reset( result );
2882 for( const auto &elem : entries ) {
2883 if( elem.second ) {
2884 result->add_group_entry( item_group_id( elem.first ), prob );
2885 } else {
2886 result->add_item_entry( itype_id( elem.first ), prob );
2887 }
2888 }
2889 return true;
2890}

2892bool Item_factory::load_string( std::vector<std::string> &vec, const JsonObject &obj,
2893 const std::string &name )
2894{
2895 bool result = false;
2896 std::string temp;
2897
2898 if( obj.has_array( name ) ) {
2899 for( const std::string line : obj.get_array( name ) ) {
2900 result |= true;
2901 vec.push_back( line );
2902 }
2903 } else if( obj.has_member( name ) ) {
2904 result |= obj.read( name, temp );
2905 vec.push_back( temp );
2906 }
2907
2908 return result;
2909}

2911void Item_factory::add_entry( Item_group &ig, const JsonObject &obj )
2912{
2913 std::unique_ptr<Item_group> gptr;
2914 int probability = obj.get_int( "prob", 100 );
2915 JsonArray jarr;
2916 if( obj.has_member( "collection" ) ) {
2917 gptr = std::make_unique<Item_group>( Item_group::G_COLLECTION, probability, ig.with_ammo,
2918 ig.with_magazine );
2919 jarr = obj.get_array( "collection" );
2920 } else if( obj.has_member( "distribution" ) ) {
2921 gptr = std::make_unique<Item_group>( Item_group::G_DISTRIBUTION, probability, ig.with_ammo,
2922 ig.with_magazine );
2923 jarr = obj.get_array( "distribution" );
2924 }
2925 if( gptr ) {
2926 for( const JsonObject job2 : jarr ) {
2927 add_entry( *gptr, job2 );
2928 }
2929 ig.add_entry( std::move( gptr ) );
2930 return;
2931 }
2932
2933 std::unique_ptr<Single_item_creator> sptr;
2934 if( obj.has_member( "item" ) ) {
2935 sptr = std::make_unique<Single_item_creator>(
2936 obj.get_string( "item" ), Single_item_creator::S_ITEM, probability );
2937 } else if( obj.has_member( "group" ) ) {
2938 sptr = std::make_unique<Single_item_creator>(
2939 obj.get_string( "group" ), Single_item_creator::S_ITEM_GROUP, probability );
2940 }
2941 if( !sptr ) {
2942 return;
2943 }
2944
2945 Item_modifier modifier;
2946 bool use_modifier = false;
2947 use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.damage, obj, "damage" );
2948 use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.dirt, obj, "dirt" );
2949 modifier.damage.first *= itype::damage_scale;
2950 modifier.damage.second *= itype::damage_scale;
2951 use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.charges, obj, "charges" );
2952 use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.count, obj, "count" );
2953 use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.ammo, obj, "ammo", ig );
2954 use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.container, obj, "container", ig );
2955 use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.contents, obj, "contents", ig );
2956 use_modifier |= load_string( modifier.custom_flags, obj, "custom-flags" );
2957 if( use_modifier ) {
2958 sptr->modifier.emplace( std::move( modifier ) );
2959 }
2960 ig.add_entry( std::move( sptr ) );
2961}

3043void Item_factory::set_use_methods_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &member,
3044 std::map<std::string, use_function> &use_methods )
3045{
3046 if( !jo.has_member( member ) ) {
3047 return;
3048 }
3049
3050 use_methods.clear();
3051 if( jo.has_array( member ) ) {
3052 for( const JsonValue entry : jo.get_array( member ) ) {
3053 if( entry.test_string() ) {
3054 std::string type = entry.get_string();
3055 emplace_usage( use_methods, type );
3056 } else if( entry.test_object() ) {
3057 auto obj = entry.get_object();
3058 std::pair<std::string, use_function> fun = usage_from_object( obj );
3059 if( fun.second ) {
3060 use_methods.insert( fun );
3061 }
3062 } else {
3063 entry.throw_error( "array element is neither string nor object." );
3064 }
3065 }
3066 } else {
3067 if( jo.has_string( member ) ) {
3068 std::string type = jo.get_string( member );
3069 emplace_usage( use_methods, type );
3070 } else if( jo.has_object( member ) ) {
3071 auto obj = jo.get_object( member );
3072 std::pair<std::string, use_function> fun = usage_from_object( obj );
3073 if( fun.second ) {
3074 use_methods.insert( fun );
3075 }
3076 } else {
3077 jo.throw_error( "member 'use_action' is neither string nor object." );
3078 }
3079
3080 }
3081}

3092
3093std::pair<std::string, use_function> Item_factory::usage_from_object( const JsonObject &obj )
3094{
3095 auto type = obj.get_string( "type" );
3096
3097 if( type == "repair_item" ) {
3098 type = obj.get_string( "item_action_type" );
3099 if( !has_iuse( type ) ) {
3100 add_actor( std::make_unique<repair_item_actor>( type ) );
3101 repair_actions.insert( type );
3102 }
3103 }
3104
3105 use_function method = usage_from_string( type );
3106
3107 if( !method.get_actor_ptr() ) {
3108 return std::make_pair( type, use_function() );
3109 }
3110
3111 method.get_actor_ptr()->load( obj );
3112 return std::make_pair( type, method );
3113}
3114
3115use_function Item_factory::usage_from_string( const std::string &type ) const
3116{
3117 auto func = iuse_function_list.find( type );
3118 if( func != iuse_function_list.end() ) {
3119 return func->second;
3120 }
3121
3122 // Otherwise, return a hardcoded function we know exists (hopefully)
3123 debugmsg( "Received unrecognized iuse function %s, using iuse::none instead", type.c_str() );
3124 return use_function();
3125}

3148item_category_id calc_category( const itype &obj )
3149{
3150 if( obj.artifact ) {
3151 return item_category_id( "artifacts" );
3152 }
3153 if( obj.gun && !obj.gunmod ) {
3154 return item_category_id( "guns" );
3155 }
3156 if( obj.magazine ) {
3157 return item_category_id( "magazines" );
3158 }
3159 if( obj.ammo ) {
3160 return item_category_id( "ammo" );
3161 }
3162 if( obj.tool ) {
3163 return item_category_id( "tools" );
3164 }
3165 if( obj.armor ) {
3166 return item_category_id( "clothing" );
3167 }
3168 if( obj.comestible ) {
3169 return obj.comestible->comesttype == "MED" ?
3170 item_category_id( "drugs" ) : item_category_id( "food" );
3171 }
3172 if( obj.book ) {
3173 return item_category_id( "books" );
3174 }
3175 if( obj.gunmod ) {
3176 return item_category_id( "mods" );
3177 }
3178 if( obj.bionic ) {
3179 return item_category_id( "bionics" );
3180 }
3181
3182 bool weap = std::any_of( obj.melee.begin(), obj.melee.end(), []( int qty ) {
3183 return qty > MELEE_STAT;
3184 } );
3185
3186 return weap ? item_category_id( "weapons" ) : item_category_id( "other" );

3200{

3218void item_group::debug_spawn()
3219{
3220 std::vector<item_group_id> groups = item_controller->get_all_group_names();
3221 uilist menu;
3222 menu.text = _( "Test which group?" );
3223 for( size_t i = 0; i < groups.size(); i++ ) {
3224 menu.entries.emplace_back( static_cast<int>( i ), true, -2, groups[i].str() );
3225 }
3226 while( true ) {
3227 menu.query();
3228 const int index = menu.ret;
3229 if( index >= static_cast<int>( groups.size() ) || index < 0 ) {
3230 break;
3231 }
3232 // Spawn items from the group 100 times
3233 std::map<std::string, int> itemnames;
3234 for( size_t a = 0; a < 100; a++ ) {
3235 const auto items = items_from( groups[index], calendar::turn );
3236 for( auto &it : items ) {
3237 itemnames[it.display_name()]++;
3238 }
3239 }
3240 // Invert the map to get sorting!
3241 std::multimap<int, std::string> itemnames2;
3242 for( const auto &e : itemnames ) {
3243 itemnames2.insert( std::pair<int, std::string>( e.second, e.first ) );
3244 }
3245 uilist menu2;
3246 menu2.text = _( "Result of 100 spawns:" );
3247 for( const auto &e : itemnames2 ) {
3248 menu2.entries.emplace_back( static_cast<int>( menu2.entries.size() ), true, -2,
3249 string_format( _( "%d x %s" ), e.first, e.second ) );
3250 }
3251 menu2.query();
3252 }

3288/** Find all templates matching the UnaryPredicate function */
3289std::vector<const itype *> Item_factory::find( const std::function<bool( const itype & )> &func )
3290{
3291 assert( frozen );
3292
3293 std::vector<const itype *> res;
3294
3295 for( const auto &e : m_templates ) {
3296 const itype *i = &e.second;
3297 if( func( *i ) ) {
3298 res.push_back( i );
